    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A general term for lapidary artists in Nahua culture, literally, "those who cut things." Tlatecque would work precious and semi-precious stones into jewelry and also cut stone mosaics.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
